<p>WAPF has several committees. If you are interested in being on a committee, please email us at <a href="mailto:director@womenagainstpaternityfraud.org">director@womenagainstpaternityfraud.org</a>.</p>
<table class="committees-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img src="images/committees/advocacycomittee.jpg" alt="advocacycomittee" /><br />
<p><strong>Advocacy Committee:</strong><br />Keeping track of legislation, conducting letter writing campaigns, lobbying legislatures, planning advocacy events, and organizing testimony.</p>
</td>
<td><img src="images/committees/tech.jpg" alt="tech" /><br />
<p><strong>Technology Committee:</strong><br />Contributing to the WAPF website and social media, including Facebook and Twitter.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><img src="images/committees/outreachcommittee.jpg" alt="outreachcommittee" /><br />
<p><strong>Outreach Committee:</strong><br />Building our relationships with other organizations and individuals who care about this issue.</p>
</td>
<td><img src="images/committees/membershipcommittee.jpg" alt="membershipcommittee" /><br />
<p><strong>Membership Committee:</strong><br />There are strength in numbers! This committee is dedicated to building our membership base.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><img src="images/committees/education.jpg" alt="education" /><br />
<p><strong>Education Committee:</strong><br />Working with the Speaker's Bureau members on conference presentations, speaking engagements, and at seminars on this issue of paternity fraud.</p>
</td>
<td><img src="images/committees/editorial.jpg" alt="editorial" /><br />
<p><strong>Editorial Committee:</strong><br />Writing news articles, commentary, press releases, and other content as needed.</p>
